<br>
One of the best (which EQ should have done 2 friggin years ago and the game would have been a god) is to let people specilize in certain abilites and actually get new things (no not the stupid spell casting spec that EQ did, that was worthless).<br>
<br>
People can actually be unique.  I play a healer and can put points into different specalizations to get new spells and to be better at something than another...<br>
<br>
This actually seperates peoples character abilites to make them unique and what they want, instead of completely generic like EQ.<br>
<br>
Put some of the new ideas in DAoC with EQ and you would get an awsome game. <p>Tuan<br><a href="http://www.dakor.net">Da`Kor</a>
